\c 1
\s1 Procedures for burnt sacrifices
\rem /s1 Sacrifices Burned Whole; The Burnt Offering; Offerings and sacrifices; Procedures for the Burnt Offering
\p
\v 1 Yahweh¬¶46173 \add вЙИsummoned\add* Mosheh¬¶46171 \add (Moses¬¶46171)\add* to the \add вЙИsacred¬¶46175\add* tent and¬¶46172 \add вЙИtold him\add*,
\v 2 вАЬTell¬¶46183 the \add вЙИIsraelis¬¶46182\add* that when anyone¬¶46186 presents an offering¬¶46205 to Yahweh¬¶46192, it must be presented from their \add ?own\add* herd or flock¬¶46201.
\v 3 If it's from the herd, it must be a bull with no¬¶46215 defects¬¶46215. It must be presented¬¶46223 \add вЙИin front¬¶46226 of\add* the entrance¬¶46219 to the \add вЙИsacred¬¶46221\add* tent to be acceptable¬¶46225 to Yahweh¬¶46227.
\v 4 \add @The owner\add* must place his hand¬¶46230 on the head of that offering¬¶46233 to be burnt¬¶46233, and¬¶46229 then¬¶46229 it will be accepted¬¶46234 \add вЙИmake him right with Yahweh\add*.
\v 5 Then¬¶46239 he must slaughter¬¶46239 the \add вЙИbull in front¬¶46244\add* of Yahweh¬¶46245, and the priests¬¶46249 (Aharons \add (Aaron's¬¶46248)\add* descendants), must present¬¶46246 the blood and splash it all around¬¶46260 the altar¬¶46259 which¬¶46261 is by the entrance¬¶46263 of the \add вЙИsacred¬¶46264\add* tent.
\v 6 Then¬¶46267 \add @the presenter\add* must skin the \add вЙИbull\add* and¬¶46271 cut it into pieces¬¶46273,
\v 7 \add вЙИMeanwhile,\add* the priest¬¶46278 Aharon's sons must put fire on the altar¬¶46282 and¬¶46275 arrange¬¶46283 wood on the fire,
\v 8 and then¬¶46289 \add *they\add* must arrange¬¶46289 the pieces¬¶46294 (including the head and the fat portions) on top of the burning¬¶46307 wood on the altar¬¶46311.
\v 9 Then¬¶46313 \add @the presenter\add* must wash the innards and the feet with¬¶46316 water¬¶46316, and the priest¬¶46318 must \add place it\add* on¬¶46316 the altar¬¶46322, \add вЙИensuring that every part is completely burnt¬¶46323 up\add* as a pleasing¬¶46327 aroma¬¶46325 for Yahweh¬¶46328.
\p
\v 10 вАЬIf the offering is from the flock¬¶46335 (i.e., a sheep¬¶46339 or a goat), then it¬¶46347 must be a healthy male¬¶46345 that's presented¬¶46347,
\v 11 and then¬¶46349 it must be slaughtered¬¶46349 on the northern¬¶46354 side of the altar facing Yahweh¬¶46356, and Aharon's¬¶46359 sons¬¶46358, the priests¬¶46360, must splash its¬¶46363 blood¬¶46363 on the altar, all around¬¶46367.
\v 12 Then¬¶46369 \add @the presenter\add* must cut it into pieces¬¶46371 and they must arrange¬¶46378 them (including the head and fat portions) on top of the burning¬¶46387 wood on the altar¬¶46391.
\v 13 Then¬¶46393 \add @the presenter\add* must wash the innards and the feet with¬¶46396 water¬¶46396, and the priest¬¶46398 must \add place it¬¶46405\add* on¬¶46396 the altar¬¶46403, \add вЙИensuring that every part is completely burnt¬¶46404 up\add* as a pleasing¬¶46408 aroma¬¶46407 for Yahweh¬¶46409.
\p
\v 14 вАЬ\add вЙИHowever,\add* if his burnt¬¶46416 offering to Yahweh¬¶46418 will be a bird, then \add вЙИit must be either a dove or a young¬¶46426 pigeon¬¶46427\add*.
\v 15 The priest¬¶46433 must present it at the altar, and then¬¶46432 twist its head off and burn¬¶46441 the head on the altar \add вЙИas he\add* drains¬¶46443 the blood¬¶46444 out onto the \add вЙИouter edge\add* of the altar.
\v 16 Then¬¶46449 he must \add вЙИpull out\add* the crop with¬¶46453 its contents¬¶46453, and¬¶46449 throw¬¶46454 it down on¬¶46453 the eastern¬¶46458 side of the altar¬¶46457 where the ashes¬¶46462 are.
\v 17 He will then¬¶46464 tear the bird \add mostly\add* apart by its wings¬¶46466 \add вЙИ(but¬¶46464 making sure that it stays as one piece)\add*, and¬¶46464 \add place it\add* on¬¶46466 the altar¬¶46472, \add вЙИensuring that every part is completely burnt¬¶46480 up\add* as a pleasing¬¶46484 aroma¬¶46483 for Yahweh¬¶46485.
\c 2
\s1 Procedures for grain offerings
\rem /s1 Procedures for the Grain Offering; The Grain Offering; Grain Offerings
\p
\v 1 вАЬWhen someone presents a grain¬¶46493 offering to Yahweh¬¶46494, it must be as fine, wheat flour¬¶46495 \add вЙИmixed with\add* \add olive\add*, and with frankincense¬¶46503 added to the top of it.
\v 2 It must be taken to the priest¬¶46510 Aharon's sons¬¶46508 who will take it \add from them\add*, then¬¶46505 take a handful¬¶46514 out, being sure to get flour¬¶46515, oil¬¶46516, and some frankincense¬¶46520, and \add вЙИthrow that memorial¬¶46525 portion¬¶46525 onto\add* the altar¬¶46526 to get completely burnt up as a pleasing¬¶46529 aroma¬¶46528 for Yahweh¬¶46530.
\v 3 Then¬¶46532 the rest of that grain¬¶46535 offering¬¶46535 will be for Aharon¬¶46536 and¬¶46537 his sons¬¶46537вАФit's a very sacred¬¶46538 part from the gifts for Yahweh¬¶46541.
\p
\v 4 вАЬWhen someone presents something baked as their grain¬¶46547 offering¬¶46547, it must be baked without leaven: either wheat flour mixed¬¶46553 with \add olive\add* oil and baked into flat buns, or else wheat flour wafers¬¶46555 with \add olive\add* oil \add вЙИspread on¬¶46554 top\add*.
\v 5 Or if your¬¶46567 grain¬¶46563 offering is done on¬¶46570 the flat pan, it¬¶46572 must be wheat flour¬¶46568 mixed¬¶46569 with¬¶46570 \add olive\add* oil¬¶46570 \add вЙИand¬¶46561 made into flat biscuits\add*
\v 6 that should then be crumbled¬¶46574 and¬¶46577 have oil¬¶46579 poured over them as \add &your\add* grain¬¶46580 offering¬¶46580.
\v 7 Or if your¬¶46588 grain¬¶46586 offering is \add deep-fried\add* in¬¶46590 a pot, it¬¶46591 must be made from wheat flour¬¶46589 with¬¶46590 \add olive\add* oil¬¶46590.
\p
\v 8 вАЬ\add Any of the above types of\add* grain¬¶46596 offering¬¶46596 to Yahweh¬¶46600 must be presented¬¶46601 to the priest¬¶46604, and¬¶46593 he will take¬¶46605 it to the altar¬¶46608.
\v 9 Then¬¶46610 he must \add take a handful\add* as a memorial¬¶46617 portion¬¶46617 to the altar¬¶46619 to get completely burnt up as a pleasing¬¶46622 aroma¬¶46621 for Yahweh¬¶46623.
\v 10 Then¬¶46625 the rest of that grain¬¶46628 offering¬¶46628 will be for Aharon¬¶46629 and¬¶46630 his sons¬¶46630вАФit's a very sacred¬¶46631 part from the gifts for Yahweh¬¶46634.
\p
\v 11 Anything that's presented¬¶46640 to Yahweh as a grain¬¶46638 offering must not be made with any rising agent, because any leaven or honey¬¶46651 mustn't be burnt as a gift to Yahweh.
\v 12 \add вЙИFoods¬¶46663 containing those\add* can be presented as a first-fruits offering, but¬¶46664 they¬¶46669 mustn't \add вЙИbe burnt\add* on the altar¬¶46666.
\v 13 \add вЙИHowever,\add* every¬¶46687 grain offering must be saltedвАФthe salt in¬¶46677 the grain offering is a reminder of our agreement, \add вЙИso it must always be present\add*.
\p
\v 14 \add вЙИFinally,\add* if you want to offer ripe grain as a grain offering to Yahweh¬¶46699, then it must be a young¬¶46700 ear of grain that's been roasted¬¶46701 over the fire¬¶46702 and presented as a grain offering of your first¬¶46698 ripe grains
\v 15 \add вЙИwith\add* \add olive\add* oil¬¶46712 on it¬¶46717 and¬¶46713 some frankincense¬¶46715 on top. That \add also becomes\add* a grain¬¶46716 offering¬¶46716,
\v 16 and the priest¬¶46720 must burn¬¶46719 a memorial¬¶46723 prtion from it with some of the crushed¬¶46724 grains¬¶46724 and some of the oil¬¶46725 and some of the incense, \add to be burnt\add* to become smoke as a gift to Yahweh¬¶46731.
